Advice to not make it lag (This is for everyone)
What felix is experiencing is mostly hopper lag, which you can reduce by placing slabs or carpets ontop of them. It makes the game pretend that items cannot go through, and that the hopper needs to stop searching for items (which causes the lag) 


Also lighting up caves helps with some lag as well

In order to see the new world generation and mega caves, you have either make a new seed, or travel far out to a part of your current seed you've not been to yet.
You didn't quite go out far enough.
Maybe use your nether shortcut and then go even further away from your main base.
You'll fine some awesome new land structures and giant caves and junk.
The update sadly just doesn't do much if anything for existing worlds.
Dark Sven looking at him in the ground laying there dead actually haunts me 11:26

PEWDS! The best way to find the new cave generation and biomes isnt to explore underground at all but instead explore the surface in places youve never been before for huge cave entrances (youll also see the new mountains this way), most huge caves connect into other huge ones which connect to others and so on so likely the first or second cave will have you exploring for hours. And i really recommend you give this update a second chance because while yes the warden isnt in yet, and believe me im just as dissapointed about that as you are the new cave and mountain generation in this update is really something to behold and i really look forward to seeing you experience it. While the pictures online can give a good idea experiencing it in your own long term world and flying around with elytra is unreal, both for the caves and mountains because yes the caves can really get that big, too big for you to see around witj just your torch so please make some nighvision potions.
